  "server": {
    "name": "io.nyc.dob",
    "title": "NYC Department of Buildings",
    "version": "0.1.0",
    "description": "Agent-native access to the NYC Department of Buildings \u2014 buildings (BIN/BBL), job filings, permits, DOB & ECB violations, complaints, and certificates of occupancy. Consolidates the browser-only legacy app layer (BIS Web, DOB NOW, eFiling) and the nightly NYC Open Data extract behind one owned surface, and adds a write workflow to file and track a DOB NOW permit application.",
    "instructions": "Use find_buildings / get_building to resolve a property by BIN, BBL, or address \u2014 the building is the join spine for everything else. find_job_filings and get_job_filing cover DOB job applications; find_permits covers issued work permits; find_violations spans both DOB (BIS) and ECB (OATH) violations (filter by violationClass); find_complaints covers 311-sourced building complaints; find_certificates_of_occupancy returns C of O records. All read tools are backed by a nightly batch extract, so data can lag the live BIS/DOB NOW systems by up to a day. file_permit_application and submit_permit_application (net-new) mutate state and require an authenticated user \u2014 confirm all filing details with the user before creating or submitting."
  },
